meta.description: Egerton 613 contains two version of the Poema Morale which were presumably copied from a shared exemplar (e.g. Hill 1977: 100). The two texts are localised in SW Worcestershire in LAEME. Scholars have noted conspicuously archaic grammar and ortography of the copies, especially of e (Hill 1977: 109).  e is by far the most consistent text in its use of accentuation. The scribes of e and E also copied other texts in the manuscript.
